## Augusta: Character Kit

## Augusta Basic Attack: Blade of the Sun
Perform up to 4 consecutive attacks dealing Electro DMG.

- **Stage 1:** Single downward slash, Electro DMG
- **Stage 2:** Wide sweeping slash, Electro DMG
- **Stage 3:** Overhead slam, Electro DMG
- **Stage 4:** Powerful forward sweep, Electro DMG
- **Heavy Attack – Steelclash:** Consume STA to attack the target, dealing Electro DMG. Press Normal Attack shortly after to perform Basic Attack Stage 2.
- **Heavy Attack – Thunderoar: Backstep (Prowess Full):** When Prowess is full, Heavy Attack – Steelclash is replaced. Augusta steps back dealing Electro DMG, consuming all Prowess. Input Normal Attack again within a brief window to perform Thunderoar: Spinslash. If Backstep is interrupted, Spinslash can still be triggered (interruption compensation).
- **Heavy Attack – Thunderoar: Spinslash:** Augusta whirls and lashes with her Broadblade, dealing Electro DMG. The Spinslash is the primary damage portion (~400%+ ATK multiplier). The Spinslash's endlag can be cancelled by the base Resonance Skill or Resonance Liberation.
- **Heavy Attack – Thunderoar: Uppercut:** When Prowess is full, pressing Jump performs Thunderoar: Uppercut (Electro DMG, consumes all Prowess) as an alternative to the Backstep path. Also triggered from Resonance Skill – Warrior's Blade when Prowess is full.
- **Dodge Counter – Thunderoar: Backstep (Ascendancy Full):** When Ascendancy is full, Normal Attack after a successful Dodge replaces the standard Dodge Counter with Dodge Counter – Thunderoar: Backstep (Electro DMG, Heavy Attack DMG). Can chain into Thunderoar: Spinslash.
- **Mid-Air Attack:** Consume STA to Plunge, dealing Electro DMG.
- **Mid-Air Dodge Counter:** Normal Attack after a successful Mid-Air Dodge for a Plunging Attack (Electro DMG, STA cost).

**Basic Attack Attribute Scaling (% of ATK, Lv.1 → Lv.10) — Stage 1 through 4 & Thunderoar: Spinslash:**

| Level | Stage 1 | Stage 2 | Stage 3 | Stage 4 | Thunderoar: Spinslash |
|-------|---------|---------|---------|---------|----------------------|
| 1     | ~34%    | ~36%    | ~43%    | ~56%    | ~408%                |
| 5     | ~44%    | ~47%    | ~56%    | ~73%    | ~531%                |
| 10    | ~66%    | ~71%    | ~84%    | ~110%   | ~800%                |

*Exact in-game per-level tables are not publicly standardized. Spinslash is confirmed to exceed 400% at Lv.1 (community, Wutheringlab). Lv.10 values are estimated using the standard ~1.5× Lv.1 multiplier curve. Consult the in-game skill screen for official values.*

## Augusta Resonance Skill: Warrior's Blade / Undying Sunlight
**Base Resonance Skill – Warrior's Blade:** Augusta performs a sweeping slash dealing Electro DMG. Restores 10% Ascendancy. Fully restores Prowess. Can trigger Thunderoar: Uppercut if Prowess was already full before casting.

**Enhanced Resonance Skill – Undying Sunlight (when Ascendancy is full, 100/100):**
A three-part aerial combo — the most important skill sequence in Augusta's kit:
- **Undying Sunlight: Strike** — Augusta charges forward on her blazing griffon, dealing Electro DMG. Provides access to Leap.
- **Undying Sunlight: Leap** — Augusta vaults skyward, dealing Electro DMG during the ascent.
- **Undying Sunlight: Plunge** — Augusta plunges from altitude and slams down her Broadblade, dealing Electro DMG classified as Heavy Attack DMG. Grants 1 stack of Majesty. This is the most important single hit in this chain and Augusta's highest-multiplier single attack (non-Liberation).

Post-S1: All three Enhanced RS parts become immune to interruption.

**Cooldown:** Warrior's Blade base skill has a standard cooldown; Undying Sunlight is only available when Ascendancy is full (not cooldown-gated independently).

**Resonance Skill Attribute Scaling (% of ATK, Lv.1 → Lv.10):**

| Level | Warrior's Blade | Undying Sunlight: Strike | Undying Sunlight: Leap | Undying Sunlight: Plunge |
|-------|----------------|--------------------------|------------------------|--------------------------|
| 1     | ~92%           | ~120%                    | ~60%                   | ~420%                    |
| 5     | ~120%          | ~156%                    | ~78%                   | ~547%                    |
| 10    | ~180%          | ~235%                    | ~117%                  | ~822%                    |

*Community-estimated ranges. Plunge is confirmed as Augusta's highest individual non-Liberation multiplier. Consult in-game for official per-level values.*

## Augusta Resonance Liberation: Sword of Eternal Oath / Sublime is the Sun
Augusta has two distinct Liberation states depending on Majesty stacks.

**Base Liberation — Sword of Eternal Oath (0–1 Majesty stack):**
Press and release Resonance Liberation. Augusta sweeps her Broadblade forward dealing Electro DMG classified as Heavy Attack DMG. Restores 40% Ascendancy.
- **Cost:** 125 Resonance Energy
- **Function:** A solid hit used during normal rotation to build Ascendancy faster. Can be used before the second Liberation is ready to maintain Ascendancy momentum.

**Enhanced Liberation — Sublime is the Sun (2 Majesty stacks):**
Hold Resonance Liberation. Costs 2 Majesty stacks (no Resonance Energy cost). Augusta generates the Ruler's Realm and enters the Sworn Allegiance state for 7 seconds.

**Sworn Allegiance State (7 seconds — time is stopped):**
- Time is completely stopped. Timers in Tower of Adversity and Whimpering Wastes pause during the full 7-second duration.
- Only Sublime is the Sun – Sunborne, Sublime is the Sun – Everbright Protector, and Dodge can be performed.
- Resonator switching is disabled during Sworn Allegiance.
- Augusta can walk on water without consuming STA in this state.
- **Sublime is the Sun – Sunborne (spam or hold Normal Attack):** Augusta swings 9 rapid Heavy Attack slashes, dealing Electro DMG each, classified as Heavy Attack DMG. Each hit is equal to 100% of Augusta's ATK.
- After 9 Sunborne hits, pressing Normal Attack or Resonance Liberation performs Sublime is the Sun – Everbright Protector.
- **Sublime is the Sun – Everbright Protector (finisher):** Augusta delivers a massive final blow dealing Electro DMG (Heavy Attack DMG). Ends Sworn Allegiance. Consumes all Crown of Wills stacks. All other Resonators are removed from the field.
- If Sworn Allegiance ends naturally (timer expires), Everbright Protector fires automatically.
- Players can early-cancel with Hold Liberation during Sworn Allegiance.

**Ruler's Realm (30s duration after Sublime is the Sun):**
- Persists for 30 seconds after Sublime is the Sun is cast, excluding the 7s of Sworn Allegiance itself.
- When Resonators in the team cast Intro Skill within Ruler's Realm: they gain a shield equal to 650 + 5% of Augusta's Max HP for 10 seconds (this effect does not stack).
- This "big shield" enables Crown of Valor stacks and Thunderflare Dominion's DEF ignore for teammates.

**Resonance Liberation Attribute Scaling (% of ATK, Lv.1 → Lv.10):**

| Level | Sword of Eternal Oath | Sunborne (per hit ×9) | Everbright Protector |
|-------|----------------------|----------------------|---------------------|
| 1     | ~180%                | 100% × 9 = 900%     | ~360%               |
| 5     | ~234%                | 100% × 9 = 900%     | ~469%               |
| 10    | ~353%                | 100% × 9 = 900%     | ~706%               |

*Sunborne multiplier (100% ATK per hit, 9 hits) is stated explicitly in-game and confirmed by multiple sources. Base Liberation and Everbright Protector scale with Liberation level. Total Liberation (Sunborne + Protector) accounts for ~53% of Augusta's total rotation damage (Wutheringlab).*

## Augusta Forte Circuit: Resource Management System
Augusta's Forte Circuit is the visual and mechanical representation of all three resources — Prowess (purple bar), Ascendancy (center circle/crown), and Majesty (gold blade icons) — displayed simultaneously.

**Prowess Generation:**
Basic Attacks, Heavy Attack – Steelclash, Mid-Air Attacks, Mid-Air Dodge Counter, Warrior's Blade, Dodge Counter, Dodge Counter – HA: Steelclash all generate Prowess. Prowess is instantly maxed by Intro Skill.

**Ascendancy Generation:**
Normal Attacks that deal damage generate Ascendancy. Intro Skill (+20%), Warrior's Blade (+10%), and Sword of Eternal Oath (+40%) also restore Ascendancy directly. The Enhanced RS combo (Undying Sunlight) consumes Ascendancy upon Plunge.

**Majesty Generation:**
Undying Sunlight: Plunge grants 1 Majesty. Augusta's Outro Skill effect (Battlesong of the Unyielding) grants 1 Majesty when the incoming Resonator casts their Outro Skill within the buff window. Blazing Valor (passive) restores 1 Majesty stack if Augusta has <1 after 4s out of combat.

**Crown of Wills Interaction:**
Crown of Wills (max 1 at S0, 2 at S1, 4 at S6) provides 15% Electro DMG Bonus per stack. Gained by casting Augusta's Outro Skill. Cleared by Everbright Protector. Also restored by Blazing Valor passive.

**Forte Circuit Attribute Scaling:**
The Forte Circuit does not have a separate DMG entry independent of the skills it unlocks. The key output is the Undying Sunlight chain (particularly Plunge) and the Thunderoar: Spinslash, both scaled under their respective skill categories above.

## Augusta Inherent Skill 1: Glory's Favor
When Augusta deals damage, she gains a shield equal to **350 + 2.5% of her Max HP** for 5 seconds, triggered once every 0.5 seconds. This shield is not transferred to incoming Resonators.

- At ~14,283 HP (Lv.90): Shield = 350 + 357 = ~707 HP
- Trigger rate: Every 0.5 seconds during active combat — near-permanent during full rotation
- Primary function: Enabling Crown of Valor echo stacks, Thunderflare Dominion's DEF ignore stacks, and the Ruler's Realm "big shield" for teammates
- Note: This shield does not meaningfully protect Augusta from damage — its strength is too low for that. It is a buff-trigger mechanic.

## Augusta Inherent Skill 2: Blazing Valor
When Augusta is out of combat for over 4 seconds, the following effects can trigger once every 4 seconds:
- If Majesty is less than 1 stack, restore 1 stack of Majesty.
- Fully restore all stacks of Crown of Wills.

This passive significantly reduces Augusta's ramp-up time, ensuring she frequently enters engagements with pre-loaded resources.

## Augusta Intro Skill: Stride of Goldenflare
**Definition:** Augusta leaps onto the battlefield and unleashes a sweeping strike, dealing Electro DMG. Upon landing:
- Fully restores Prowess (100/100 instantly)
- Restores 20% Ascendancy
- Post-S1: Grants 1 stack of Crown of Wills
- Post-S4: Increases ATK of all Resonators in the team by 20% for 30 seconds

**Intro Skill Attribute Scaling (% of ATK, Lv.1 → Lv.10):**

| Level | Intro Skill DMG |
|-------|----------------|
| 1     | ~80%           |
| 5     | ~104%          |
| 10    | ~157%          |

*Estimated from community sources. Confirm exact values in-game.*

## Augusta Outro Skill: Battlesong of the Unyielding
**Definition:** The next Resonator switched onto the field gains the following effects for 14 seconds (ends immediately if they are switched out):
- Gain **15% DMG Amplification for all Attributes** (applies to all damage types dealt by the incoming Resonator)
- If the Resonator with this buff casts their Outro Skill within the 14-second window → Augusta gains **1 stack of Majesty** and **1 stack of Crown of Wills**

This Outro mechanic is the lynchpin of Augusta's team rotation: the incoming teammate must chain their Outro Skill within 14 seconds to give Augusta the Majesty stack needed for her second, time-stopping Liberation. Without this interaction, Augusta needs to generate both Majesty stacks entirely from Undying Sunlight: Plunge (requiring two full Ascendancy cycles — significantly slower).

**Outro Skill Attribute Scaling:**
- DMG Amplification: 15% (flat, all-attribute) — does not scale with Outro level
- Buff duration: 14 seconds (flat)
- Consult in-game for any DMG values associated with the Outro animation itself.

