## Augusta: Echo Sets

## Augusta Echo Sets: Best Options
**Best Echo Set — Crown of Valor (3pc) + Void Thunder (2pc):**
- **Crown of Valor 3pc bonus:** Upon gaining a Shield, increase the Resonator's ATK by 6% and Crit DMG by 4% for 4 seconds. This effect can be triggered once every 0.5s, stacking up to 5 times. At max stacks: +30% ATK and +20% Crit DMG.
- **Void Thunder 2pc bonus:** +10% Electro DMG Bonus.
- **Why it works:** Augusta's Glory's Favor passive triggers a new shield every 0.5 seconds during combat — matching the Crown of Valor stack interval exactly. With proper rotation, she maintains 5/5 stacks for most of her active time, giving a substantial +30% ATK and +20% Crit DMG without any additional input.

**Alternative Echo Set — Void Thunder (5pc full set):**
- 2pc: +10% Electro DMG Bonus
- 5pc: After casting Intro Skill or Resonance Skill, deal 20% more Electro DMG for 15s
- Use when Crown of Valor is not yet fully farmed. Still very competitive, especially before Crown of Valor set is established.

## Augusta Echo Sets: Best Main Echo
**The False Sovereign (4-Cost Echo — Recommended):**
- Set: Crown of Valor (contributes to the 3pc bonus)
- Main Echo Skill: Transform into the False Sovereign and dash forward in a spinning strike, dealing 55.35% Electro DMG 4 times. Start with 2 charges; gain 1 charge every 8s, up to 2 charges.
- Passive bonus (equipped in main slot): +12% Electro DMG Bonus + 12% Heavy Attack DMG Bonus
- Upon casting Intro Skill, the False Sovereign is also summoned to deal 405% Electro DMG.
- **Why it's Best-in-Slot:** Provides two of Augusta's most important damage type bonuses simultaneously (Electro and Heavy Attack), has two charges enabling flexible rotation use, and offers a bonus Intro Skill proc.

**Alternative Main Echo — Impermanence Heron or other 4-Cost Havoc/Electro Echoes:** For players without False Sovereign, any 4-Cost Echo with Crit Rate main stat serves as an acceptable placeholder.

## Augusta Echo Sets: Echo Stat Priority

**4-Cost Echo Main Stat:**
- S0/S1: Crit Rate (priority — to hit the 70–80% Crit Rate target)
- S2–S5: Crit Rate or Crit DMG (flex depending on current substat rolls)
- S6: Crit DMG (Crit Rate naturally overcaps via Crown of Wills × 4 stacks + S2/S6 passive)

**3-Cost Echo Main Stats:** Electro DMG Bonus × 2 (NOT ATK% — using ATK% instead results in approximately 4% damage loss, equivalent to one effective substat)

**1-Cost Echo Main Stat:** ATK%

## Augusta Echo Sets: Substat Priority
1. Crit Rate / Crit DMG (balanced — equal value at S0; favor Crit DMG at S2+)
2. Heavy Attack DMG Bonus (notably higher value than ATK% for Augusta)
3. ATK%
4. Flat ATK (last resort)
5. Energy Regen: ~120% is sufficient for standard rotation; minimum needed for consistent Liberation cycling

